Shanghai Secco in Process of Starting Naphtha Cracker, ICIS Says

-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 
2011-09-27T05:29:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/shanghai-secco-in-process-of-starting-naphtha-cracker-icis-says.html
Shanghai Secco Petrochemical Co. is
resuming its naphtha cracker after a fire occurred this month at
its production site in the Chinese city, ICIS reported, citing
people familiar with the company it didn’t identify.  Angela Qian, a public affairs manager at Shanghai Secco,
couldn’t immediately comment on plans to start the cracker when
reached by phone by Bloomberg News today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ann Koh in Singapore at 
 akoh15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alexander Kwiatkowski at 
 akwiatkowsk2@bloomberg.net  